headline: Should You Buy Carnival Stock Right Now?
summary: Carnival continues to report record quarterly revenue as demand remains historically high for cruise vacations.  Shares of Carnival (NYSE: CCL) (NYSE: CUK) have more than doubled since bottoming out in 2022, but the stock has been volatile this year.  While strong demand for cruises has fueled higher revenue for Carnival, Wall Street is focused on risks that could derail its momentum.
